entry.def: If you refer to someone as an overlord, you mean that they have great power and are likely to use it in a bad way.

example.ex: We really don't want to be the overlords of the Palestinian population...
example.tran: 我们真的并不希望成为巴勒斯坦人民的太上皇。

example.ex: The running of Welsh rugby was left in chaos yesterday after a vote of no confidence in the game's overlords.
example.tran: 昨天，在对威尔士橄榄球界几位巨头投了不信任票后，该运动的管理陷入一片混乱。

entry.def: In former times, an overlord was someone who had power over many people.

example.ex: Henry II was the first king to be recognized as overlord of Ireland.
example.tran: 亨利二世是第一位被承认为爱尔兰领主的国王。
